April 26, 2016 marks the 30th anniversary of the Chernobyl nuclear disaster .
In recent years, visits to the nuclear blast site have increased exponentially .
Visitors are banned from touching anything, eating or drinking any food that does not come from outside the zone .
The Exclusion Zone, a nearly 50kilometre (31-mile) radius of the site, is highly regulated and permitted only as part of an organised private tour .